Create a Pi extension that adds `/push`.

When invoked, `/push` should directly synthesize a Git Bash tool call to push the current worktree to GitHub main, instead of first asking the LLM what command to run.

It should also synthesize a user message:

"Please push this worktree to GitHub main."

The success path should be low-latency and mostly deterministic. If the command exits non-zero, pass stdout/stderr/exit code back to the LLM so it can diagnose and handle the failure.

Please keep the implementation small, readable, and consistent with Pi’s extension style.
